Error: Error: "Java.Io.IOException: An Existing Connection Was Forcibly Closed By The Remote Host"

Solution: 1. Check if the Minecraft server is up-to-date with the latest version. 
2. Restart the Minecraft server by closing it and reopening it. 
3. Check if the firewall or antivirus software is blocking the Minecraft server. Add the server to the list of exceptions in the firewall/antivirus software or temporarily disable them. 
4. Ensure that the server properties file is set correctly
